        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 4:32PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 432 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles north of Nutt, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Nutt, Derry, Lake Valley, Uvas Valley, and Macho Springs.

This includes Interstate 25 in New Mexico between mile markers 51 and
52.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
